Articles.Content:
KSP Version: 1.9.1, Windows, 64-bit, Steam

What happens: Game crashes when I launch it

Mods / Add-ons: None

Steps to replicate: Click the launch button in Steam or launch via desktop shortcut

Laptop Specs:

Processor: AMD A10-5745M APU with Radeon(tm) HD Graphics 2.10 GHz

RAM: 12 GB

64-bit

Other notes/Video/Log files:

- I bought the game yesterday. When I downloaded it for the first time, it crashed when I tried to launch the game. Same repeats every time I try to open it.

- I tried a lot to fix the problem, but nothing worked (for example: verify integrity of game files, reinstall).

- KSP Crash Video (imgur) --> Video of what happens when I try to launch KSP

It looks like you are using very old video drivers, could you try with a recent version.

Or else you could try opengl with the -force-opengl startup parameter.

https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Startup_parameters

d3d11 is a graphics crash. They are often caused by outdated graphics drivers which can't handle some of the newer code- KSP had a significant Unity engine upgrade in version 1.8 and quite a few people have had issues since then, myself included! Try updating your graphics drivers to the most recent version.
